2948:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****         /* This function should not be called by application code hence the
2949:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          * 'Restricted' in its name.  It is not part of the public API.  It is
2950:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          * designed for use by kernel code, and has special calling requirements.
2951:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          * It can result in vListInsert() being called on a list that can only
2952:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          * possibly ever have one item in it, so the list will be fast, but even
2953:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          * so it should be called with the scheduler locked and not from a critical
2954:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          * section. */
2955:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c **** 
2956:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****         /* Only do anything if there are no messages in the queue.  This function
2957:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          *  will not actually cause the task to block, just place it on a blocked
2958:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          *  list.  It will not block until the scheduler is unlocked - at which
2959:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          *  time a yield will be performed.  If an item is added to the queue while
2960:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          *  the queue is locked, and the calling task blocks on the queue, then the
2961:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/queue.c ****          *  calling task will be immediately unblocked when the queue is unlocked. */
